wikipedia_page.main: Jordan Gideon Archer (born 12 April 1993) is a professional footballer who plays as a goalkeeper for EFL Championship club Queens Park Rangers and the Scotland national team. Archer has previously played for Tottenham Hotspur, Harrow Borough, Bishop's Stortford, Wycombe Wanderers, Northampton Town, Millwall, Oxford United, Fulham, Motherwell and Middlesbrough. He represents Scotland internationally, and made his full international debut in May 2018.
